cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on building a traffic simulation pipeline for emergency management, which involves creating maps, generating demand, identifying bottlenecks, improving traffic management policies, and analyzing results. This covers a wide range of topics related to computer engineering (cs.CE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and simulation (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of robotics (cs.RO) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) may also be relevant in emergency management scenarios.
